'''Logan Evans Costa''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈlo.ɡɐn ˈɛ.vɐns ˈkɔʃ.tɐ|lang}}<!----The player was born in France. Check for sources if his first names are pronounced in a “Portuguese way” or in a “French way”.---->; born 1 April 2001) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]. Born in France, he represents the  [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

Costa is a former French youth international, having represented them at [[France national under-16 football team|U16]] and [[France national under-17 football team|U17]] level, before switching to play for Cape Verde in 2022.

==Early life==
Costa was born in [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|Saint-Denis]], [[Île-de-France]],<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|date=20 August 2021|title=Transferts : Logan Costa (Reims) vers Toulouse|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-logan-costa-reims-vers-toulouse/1279061|access-date=2021-12-18|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|archive-date=21 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230521162132/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-logan-costa-reims-vers-toulouse/1279061|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|last=Valente|first=Toni|date=4 July 2021|title=Mercato : Logan Costa ne prolongera pas avec le Stade de Reims|url=https://madeinfoot.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-mercato-logan-costa-ne-prolongera-pas-avec-le-stade-de-reims-348199.html|website=MadeinFoot|publisher=[[Ouest-France]]}}</ref> to a [[Cape Verde]]an family.<ref name=":7">{{Cite web|date=2021-07-05|title=Stade de Reims, Logan Costa refuse de prolonger|url=https://abonne.lunion.fr/id272529/article/2021-07-05/football-ligue-1-stade-de-reims-logan-costa-refuse-de-prolonger|access-date=2021-12-18|website=[[L'Union (French newspaper)|L'Union]]|language=fr|quote=Pour le défenseur axial franco-cap-verdien, international U20, qui vient de changer d'agent, le club rémois ne lui offre plus les garanties}}</ref><ref name=":9">{{Cite web|title=Cinq choses à savoir sur Logan Costa, le nouveau défenseur toulousain|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/cinq-choses-a-savoir-sur-logan-costa-le-nouveau-defenseur-toulousain,59104.html|access-date=2021-12-19|website=LesViolets.com|language=fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
Having started to play football in [[Argenteuil]], [[Val-d'Oise]], Costa joined the youth academy of [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in 2016.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Musset|first=Hervé|date=2020-01-24|title=Football (National 2) : Logan Costa, ce jeune discret du Stade de Reims qui s'ouvre|url=https://abonne.lunion.fr/id126055/article/2020-01-24/football-national-2-logan-costa-ce-jeune-discret-du-stade-de-reims-qui-souvre|access-date=2021-12-18|website=[[L'Union (French newspaper)|L'Union]]|language=fr|quote=d'abord passé par Argenteuil avant de poursuivre sa formation au Stade de Reims depuis 2016, avait trop envie de jouer.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-02-28|title=Logan costa du RFC Argenteuil signe au Stade de Reims…|url=https://www.panamefoot.fr/logan-costa-du-rfc-argenteuil-signe-au-stade-de-reims/|access-date=2021-12-18|website=Panamefoot|language=fr-FR|archive-date=18 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218170817/https://www.panamefoot.fr/logan-costa-du-rfc-argenteuil-signe-au-stade-de-reims/|url-status=live}}</ref>

A player in Reims's [[2018–19 Championnat National 2|Championnat National 2]] reserve starting in the 2018–19 season, Costa captained the side during the following campaign.<ref name=":9"/><ref name=":0" /><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|last=Sabrié|first=Clémentine|date=2020-07-11|title=Le défenseur central Logan Costa prêté au Mans FC par le Stade de Reims|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/le-defenseur-central-logan-costa-prete-au-mans-fc-par-le-stade-de-reims-1594464038|access-date=2021-12-19|publisher=[[France Bleu]]|location=Le Mans|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=10 July 2020|title=Logan Costa prêté au Mans (National)|url=https://www.stade-de-reims.com/logan-costa-prete-au-mans-national/|access-date=2021-12-19|publisher=[[Stade de Reims]]}}</ref> With a few first-team appearances in [[Ligue 1]] games,<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-12-07|title=Le Stade de Reims avec Sissoko et Costa face à Saint-Étienne|url=https://abonne.lunion.fr/id114678/article/2019-12-07/football-ligue-1-le-stade-de-reims-avec-sissoko-et-costa-face-saint-etienne|access-date=2021-12-19|website=[[L'Union (French newspaper)|L'Union]]|language=fr}}</ref> he was loaned to [[Championnat National]] side [[Le Mans FC|Le Mans]] for the [[2020–21 Championnat National|2020–21 season]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":5"/>

With Le Mans newly relegated from [[2019–20 Ligue 2|Ligue 2]], he was one of the standout players in the team, and a revelation of the Championnat National, starting and playing the entirety of 26 games, as the club only narrowly missed the promotion play-offs.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":6" /><ref name=":7" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":8">{{Cite web|date=2021-08-18|title=Logan Costa (Stade de Reims) se rapproche de Toulouse|url=https://abonne.lunion.fr/id285031/article/2021-08-18/football-ligue-1-logan-costa-stade-de-reims-se-rapproche-de-toulouse|access-date=2021-12-19|website=[[L'Union (French newspaper)|L'Union]]|language=fr}}</ref>

After this promising loan spell, Costa was offered a contract extension by Reims, but chose to look elsewhere in search of more game time.<ref name=":6" /><ref name=":7" /> With one year left on his contract, several clubs from France, Italy and Germany were interested in signing him.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":6" /><ref name=":8"/> He was eventually transferred to [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] in August 2021.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />

Costa made his professional debut for Toulouse on 13 November 2021, starting and playing every minute of a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] victory over [[FC Libourne|Libourne]] in the [[Coupe de France]], in which he helped his team keep a clean sheet.<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 November 2021|title=Coupe de France - 7e tour : découvrez le 11 de départ du TFC pour le match à Libourne (5e division)|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/11/13/coupe-de-france-7e-tour-decouvrez-le-11-de-depart-du-tfc-pour-le-match-a-libourne-5e-division-9925543.php|access-date=2021-12-18|website=[[La Dépêche du Midi|La Dépêche]]|location=Toulouse, Haute-Garonne|language=fr|archive-date=18 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211218142023/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/11/13/coupe-de-france-7e-tour-decouvrez-le-11-de-depart-du-tfc-pour-le-match-a-libourne-5e-division-9925543.php|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Assemat|first=Anthony|date=20 November 2021|title=Toulouse. Choc au sommet, record de spectateurs... Tous au Stadium pour TFC-Sochaux !|url=https://actu.fr/occitanie/toulouse_31555/toulouse-choc-au-sommet-record-de-spectateurs-tous-au-stadium-pour-tfc-sochaux_46448050.html|access-date=2021-12-18|website={{ill|actu.fr|fr}}|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Polizzi|first=Cédric|date=14 November 2021|title=Libourne FC 0-0 (1 tab à 3) TFC : La masterclass de Pettersson, j'y étais pour vous|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/libourne-fc-0-0-1-tab-a-3-tfc-la-masterclass-de-pettersson-j-y-etais-pour-vous,60048.html|access-date=2021-12-18|website=LesViolets.com|language=fr}}</ref> Starting the [[2021–22 Toulouse FC season|season]] behind [[Rasmus Nicolaisen]], [[Bafodé Diakité]] and [[Anthony Rouault]], with a team aiming for promotion,<ref>{{Cite web|date=11 November 2021|title=FC Libourne - TFC : Isak Pettersson, Logan Costa, Steve Mvoue, Mamady Bangré, quatre joueurs à relancer|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/fc-libourne-tfc-isak-pettersson-logan-costa-steve-mvoue-mamady-bangre-quatre-joueurs-a-relancer,60005.html|access-date=2021-12-19|website=LesViolets.com|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Desprez|first=Patrick|date=20 September 2021|title=TFC, pourquoi ça marche ? Ado, Genreau, les recrues, quel cru !|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/09/20/dossier-tfc-pourquoi-ca-marche-ado-genreau-les-recrues-quel-cru-9801346.php|access-date=2021-12-19|website=[[La Dépêche du Midi|La Dépêche]]|location=Toulouse, Haute-Garonne|language=fr|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219235602/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/09/20/dossier-tfc-pourquoi-ca-marche-ado-genreau-les-recrues-quel-cru-9801346.php|url-status=live}}</ref> Costa first only made bench appearances in [[2021–22 Ligue 2|Ligue 2]].<ref name=":10">{{Cite web|date=5 December 2021|title=Ligue 2 - 17e journée : voici les 18 Toulousains retenus par Philippe Montanier pour le déplacement à Niort ce lundi soir|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/12/05/ligue-2-17e-journee-voici-les-18-toulousains-retenus-par-philippe-montanier-pour-le-deplacement-a-niort-ce-lundi-soir-9973216.php|access-date=2021-12-19|website=[[La Dépêche du Midi|La Dépêche]]|location=Toulouse, Haute-Garonne|language=fr|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219235605/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/12/05/ligue-2-17e-journee-voici-les-18-toulousains-retenus-par-philippe-montanier-pour-le-deplacement-a-niort-ce-lundi-soir-9973216.php|url-status=live}}</ref> However, he established himself as a regular starter in the Coupe de France, even scoring his first goal against [[Trélissac-Antonne Périgord FC|Trélissac]].<ref name=":10" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Cassé|first=Josué|date=28 November 2021|title=CdF : Toulouse vient à bout de Trélissac et se qualifie pour les 32e|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a5651078808250114002-cdf-toulouse-vient-a-bout-de-trelissac-et-se-qualifie-pour-les-32e|access-date=2021-12-19|website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}}|language=fr|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219235613/https://www.footmercato.net/a5651078808250114002-cdf-toulouse-vient-a-bout-de-trelissac-et-se-qualifie-pour-les-32e|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Faham|first=Bryan|date=2021-11-28|title=Coupe de France. Qualification dans les dernières minutes pour le TFC|url=https://www.lejournaltoulousain.fr/sport/coupe-de-france-qualification-derniere-minutes-pour-le-tfc-137285/|access-date=2021-12-19|website={{ill|Le Journal toulousain|fr}}|language=fr-FR}}</ref>

On 22 August 2024, Costa joined [[La Liga]] club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] on a six-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Villarreal CF sign Logan Costa |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/villarreal-cf-sign-logan-costa/ |publisher=[[Villarreal CF]] |access-date=23 August 2024 |date=22 August 2024 }}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 26 August, coming on as a substitute in a league win over [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Villarreal 4–3 Celta Vigo (Aug 26, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/704688/celta-vigo-villarreal |publisher=[[ESPN]] |access-date=15 September 2024 |date=26 August 2024}}</ref> On 14 September, he scored his first goal for Villarreal in a 2–1 victory against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Feargal |last=Brennan |title=La Liga Round Up: Villarreal go third as Sevilla seal first win of 2024/25 |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2024/09/15/la-liga-round-up-villarreal-third-sevilla-seal-win |website=Football España |access-date=15 September 2024 |date=15 September 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Costa was a youth international for France, playing with the [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]] and [[France national under-17 football team|under-17]] teams.<ref name=":5"/><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|last=Verger|first=Adrien|date=20 August 2021|title=TFC : Logan Costa est officiellement un joueur toulousain|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2021/08/20/tfc-logan-costa-est-officiellement-un-joueur-toulousain-9742173.php|access-date=2021-12-19|website=[[La Dépêche du Midi|La Dépêche]]|location=Toulouse, Haute-Garonne|language=fr}}</ref> He was also selected for the [[France national under-19 football team|under-19s]] and [[France national under-20 football team|under-20s]], without playing any official games in a period where most of them were canceled due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name=":9"/><ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|last=Ptak|first=Guillaume|date=20 August 2021|title=Football Ligue 2 : le défenseur du Stade de Reims Logan Costa s'engage avec le Toulouse Football Club|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/occitanie/haute-garonne/toulouse/football-ligue-2-le-defenseur-du-stade-de-reims-logan-costa-s-engage-avec-le-toulouse-football-club-2219971.html|access-date=2021-12-19|publisher=[[France 3]]|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|date=20 August 2021|title=Le défenseur Logan Costa s'engage avec le TéFéCé !|url=https://www.toulousefc.com/fr/le-defenseur-logan-costa-sengage-avec-le-tefece|access-date=2021-12-19|publisher=[[Toulouse FC]]|language=fr}}</ref>

On 16 March 2022, he received his first international call-up for the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcf.cv/selecao-nacional-aa-os-convocados-para-os-tres-jogos-amigaveis-em-marco/|title=Seleção Nacional AA: Os convocados para os três jogos amigáveis em Março|publisher=[[Cape Verdean Football Federation]]|date=16 March 2022|language=pt|access-date=17 March 2022|archive-date=28 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528163508/https://fcf.cv/selecao-nacional-aa-os-convocados-para-os-tres-jogos-amigaveis-em-marco/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1955308/cabo-verde-divulga-lista-extensa-de-convocados-bebe-e-estreia|title=Cabo Verde divulga lista extensa de convocados. Bebé é estreia|publisher=Notícias ao Minuto|date=16 March 2022|language=pt}}</ref> He debuted with Cape Verde in a 2–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] win over [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-guadalupe/cabo-verde/2022433474/events|title=Live events Guadalupe vs Cape Verde – International Friendly 2022|website=besoccer.com|access-date=24 March 2022|archive-date=28 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528132654/https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-guadalupe/cabo-verde/2022433474/events|url-status=live}}</ref> He was later named in Cape Verde's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://khelnow.com/football/2023-12-world-football-cape-verde-squad-afcon|title=Cape Verde announce 26-man squad for AFCON 2023|publisher=Khel Now|date=31 December 2023}}</ref> where he played in all five of their matches before they were eliminated in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698137/south-africa-cape-verde-islands|title=South Africa 0–0 Cape Verde (Feb 3, 2024) Final Score|publisher=ESPN|date=3 February 2024}}</ref>

==Controversy==
On 14 May 2023, Costa reportedly refused to participate in a Ligue 1 match against [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] due to the game being part of a league-wide campaign against [[homophobia]], with players wearing shirts with rainbow-themed decorations. However, he later denied the allegation that he refused to play in the match. <ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Toulouse FC's Players, Including Morocco's Aboukhlal, Refuse LGBTQ+ Jerseys |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/05/355445/toulouse-fcs-players-including-moroccos-aboukhlal-refuse-lgbtq-jerseys |access-date=2024-05-24 |website=www.moroccoworldnews.com |language=en |archive-date=14 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514191031/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/05/355445/toulouse-fcs-players-including-moroccos-aboukhlal-refuse-lgbtq-jerseys |url-status=live }}</ref>

